content.text:
The vestibular system can be stimulated or irritated by an infection of the inner ear or by a tumor (arrow) pressing on the vestibulocochlear nerve. Which of the following would NOT occur? <image 1> 

A. Decreased auditory acuity.
B. Vertigo.
C. Tinnitis.
D. Loss of facial sensation.

We refer to Wikipedia articles on anatomy for help. The vestibulocochlear nerve is responsible for hearing and balance, so when it is irritated, vertigo, tinnitus, and decreased auditory acuity may occur. However, loss of facial sensation will not occur.

Therefore, the answer is D.
